data.title: Must Have piCture pOlish Shades Plus Nail Art
data.meta_description: 8 Must Have piCture pOlish Shades Plus Nail Art
data.text:
Press Sample

I have 6 previously released piCture pOlish shades to share with you today that are fairly well known and some classic piCture pOlish shades.

While I love the flare of sparkle and shimmer in polishes, I was first drawn to piCture pOlish by their cremes and the beautiful shades and flawless application, but you really can’t dismiss their shimmer and sparkle either!

Let’s take a look at these 6 shades and then some stamping I did.

Sky

Sky is a light sky blue creme. Flawless in application and I used 3 thin coats for these photos.

Tiffany

Tiffany is a flawless eggshell blue with a touch of mint. I used 2 coats for these photos and if you can only have 1 creme from piCture pOlish, this should be it.

Violet Femme

I have been eyeing this beauty for awhile and it was worth the wait. Violet Femme is an intense violet creme. I used 2 coats for these photos.

Vampire

Vampire is a shade that I don’t know how I missed! This is a blood red jelly that looks like blood on the nails. I know that sounds gruesome, but it’s true. I used 3 thin coats for these photos.

Electric Dream

Electric Dream was made in collaboration with Nail Polish Anon. Electric Dream is a coral scattered holo with gold sparks. I used 2 coats for these photos.

Bridget

Bridget is a deep red scattered holographic. I currently have this on my toes (don’t worry, I don’t do feet photos!) I used 2 coats for these photos.

Stamping With Violet Femme & Scandal

I keep playing with the Vampy Chameleon shades I purchased and when I put on Violet Femme I thought it would be the perfect base to stamp over with Scandal! I love that it’s fairly subtle from a distance but has the right amount of shimmer and holo to give it some life.

Price: AU$11.00 – $13.00 Each

Where To Buy: piCture pOlish Website or one of the stockists in their Network from all over the world!

Social Media: Facebook | Twitter | InstaGram |Youtube|Pinterest|Google+
